The end goal workflow of the gem:
  1.  - "i18n-lazy-generator generate [file path] [--interactive] [--no-common]"
      - Detect given path format (Folder/HTML/HAML/jade/etc.)
      - Process into HTML
      - Parse HTML file and divide into text-blocks (keys)
      = For each text-block:
        - Generate .YML "key: content" pair and add to keys
          - Generate key name ("_html", collisions)
          - Generate key content (substitute erb with i18n vars)
        - Generate HTML inline key
          - Generate ERB code
          - Using var interpolation
        ? Process HTML inline key into source file format if needed (like HAML)
        ? Ask user if modification is correct
        - Modify files and continue

  2.  - "i18n-lazy-generator rename [file path] [key] [new name]"
  3.  - "i18n-lazy-generator delete [file path] [key]"
  4.  - "i18n-lazy-generator common [file path] [key]"
  5.  - "i18n-lazy-generator uncommon [file path] [key]"


Modules:
  Finder
  Generator
    KeyNameGenerator
    KeyContentGenerator
    InlineKeyGenerator
  Replacer
    Content Replacer
    Key Replacer
